glide /ɡlaɪd/

(gliding,glided,glides) 

1. V-I If you glide somewhere, you move silently and in a smooth and effortless way. 滑行 

例： Waiters glide between tightly packed tables bearing trays of pasta. 侍者们托着一盘盘的意大利面食在拥挤的餐桌间自如穿行。 

2. V-I When birds or aeroplanes glide , they float on air currents. 滑翔 

例： Our only companion is the wandering albatross, which glides effortlessly and gracefully behind the yacht. 我们惟一的伴侣是那只漂泊信天翁，它轻快优雅地滑翔在游艇后面。

